  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Food Manufacturing Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>📌 Key Responsibilities</p><p>• \tProduction Oversight</p><p>• \tSupervise and coordinate day-to-day food manufacturing activities.</p><p>• \tEnsure production schedules are met while maintaining product quality.</p><p>• \tMonitor workflow, equipment performance, and resource allocation.</p><p>• \tQuality Assurance & Compliance</p><p>• \tEnforce food safety standards (HACCP, GMP, ISO, or local regulations).</p><p>• \tConduct routine inspections and audits to maintain hygiene and sanitation.</p><p>• \tEnsure compliance with health, safety, and environmental policies.</p><p>• \tTeam Leadership</p><p>• \tManage, train, and motivate production staff.</p><p>• \tAssign tasks, monitor performance, and provide feedback.</p><p>• \tFoster a culture of accountability, teamwork, and continuous improvement.</p><p>• \tProcess & Efficiency Improvement</p><p>• \tIdentify bottlenecks and implement solutions to optimize productivity.</p><p>• \tRecommend process improvements and cost-saving initiatives.</p><p>• \tCollaborate with R&D and quality teams on new product launches.</p><p>• \tReporting & Documentation</p><p>• \tMaintain accurate production records, reports, and logs.</p><p>• \tTrack KPIs such as yield, waste, downtime, and labor efficiency.</p><p>• \tReport issues to senior management and propose corrective actions.</p><p>Qualifications</p><p>• \tDiploma/Degree in Food Science, Food Technology, Engineering, or related field.</p><p>• \tMinimum 3–5 years of experience in food manufacturing or production supervision.</p><p>• \tCertifications in HACCP, GMP, or ISO standards (preferred).</p><p>📊 Performance Indicators</p><p>• \tAchievement of production targets.</p><p>• \tCompliance with food safety and quality standards.</p><p>• \tReduction in waste, downtime, and production errors.</p><p>• \tEmployee engagement and retention within the production team.<br /></p><p>Work Hours<br />• Monday - Sunday : 5 am - 3 pm</p><p>• 1 day off in lieu will be given for the replacement of working on Sunday and public holidays\n</p>",
